      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/expert-review-preparation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "A key concept of the MZmine 2 software design is the strict separation of core functionality and data processing modules, with emphasis on easy usability and support for high-resolution spectra processing... We focused on three main aims during the software design and implementation. First, the framework should be flexible and allow for easy and straightforward development of new data processing modules... Second, the graphical interface of the application should be intuitive and easy to use... The third goal was to provide good support for processing high-resolution MS data",
      "asbval:note": "The paper does state goals of flexibility, usability, and extensibility, but the scope description is about a meta-skill for validating software projects before review. The paper itself is the software description, not a guide to the validation process. The example goals cited ('user-friendly, flexible, easily extendable') are present in the paper, but the scope's framing as a skill/workflow for validation is not addressed by the paper.",
